 150class Seed:
 151    def __init__(self, station_code, location_code, coordinates: Coordinates,
 152                 elevation: float = 0):
 153        """
 154        Contains a location
 155        :param station_code: station code
 156        :param instrument_code: location code
 157        :param coordinates:
 158        """
 159
 160        self.station = station_code
 161        self.location = location_code
 162        self.coordinates = coordinates
 163        self.elevation = elevation
 164
 165    def __repr__(self):
 166        return f'label (station.location): {self.station}.{self.location}\n' \
 167               f'                       x: {self.coordinates.x:0.2f}\n' \
 168               f'                       y: {self.coordinates.y:0.2f}\n' \
 169               f'                       z: {self.coordinates.z:0.2f}\n' \
 170               f'               elevation: {self.elevation:0.2f}\n' \
 171               f'       coordinate_system: {self.coordinates.coordinate_system}\n'
 172
 173    def __str__(self):
 174        return self.__repr__()
 175
 176    @property
 177    def x(self):
 178        return self.coordinates.x
 179
 180    @property
 181    def y(self):
 182        return self.coordinates.y
 183
 184    @property
 185    def z(self):
 186        return self.coordinates.z
 187
 188    @property
 189    def loc(self):
 190        return self.coordinates.loc
 191
 192    @property
 193    def label(self):
 194        return f'{self.station}_{self.location}'
 195
 196    @property
 197    def instrument_code(self):
 198        return self.label
 199
 200    @property
 201    def T(self):
 202        return np.array(self.coordinates.loc).T
 203
 204    @classmethod
 205    def random_in_grid(cls, grid: Grid, n_seeds: int = 1) -> 'List[Seed]':
 206        """
 207        Generate a random point within the grid boundary
 208        :param grid: a grid object
 209        :type grid: uquake.grid.base.Grid or an object inheriting from Grid
 210        :param n_seeds: number of locations to generate
 211        :type n_seeds: int
 212        :return: a list of Location objects
 213
 214        :example:
 215        >> from uquake.grid.base import Grid
 216        >> from uquake.grid.nlloc import Location
 217        >> grid_dimensions = [10, 10, 10]
 218        >> grid_spacing = [1, 1, 1]
 219        >> grid_origin = [0, 0, 0]
 220        >> grid = Grid(grid_dimensions, grid_spacing, grid_origin, value=1)
 221        >> locations = Location.random_in_grid(grid, n_location=10)
 222        """
 223
 224        codes = generate_unique_instrument_code(n_codes=n_seeds)
 225        seeds = []
 226
 227        for i, (point, code) in enumerate(zip(grid.generate_random_points_in_grid(
 228                n_points=n_seeds), codes)):
 229            station_code = code.split('_')[0]
 230            location_code = code.split('_')[1]
 231            coordinates = Coordinates(point[0], point[1], point[2])
 232            seeds.append(cls(station_code, location_code, coordinates))
 233
 234        return seeds

 237class SeedEnsemble:
 238
 239    def __init__(self, seeds: List[Seed] = [], units: GridUnits = GridUnits.METER):
 240        """
 241        specifies a series of source location from an inventory object
 242        :param seeds: a list of locations containing at least the location,
 243        and location label
 244        :param units: units of measurement used to express x, y, and z
 245        :type units: str must be a valid unit of measurement as defined by the
 246        GridUnits class
 247        :type seeds: list of dictionary
 248
 249        :Example:
 250
 251        >>> seed = Seed('station_code', 'location_code', Coordinates(0, 0, 0))
 252        >>> seeds = SeedEnsemble([seed])
 253
 254        """
 255
 256        self.units = units
 257        self.seeds = seeds
 258
 259    def __len__(self):
 260        return len(self.seeds)
 261
 262    def __getitem__(self, item):
 263        return self.seeds[item]
 264
 265    def __repr__(self):
 266        return f'{self.units}\n' + '\n'.join(self.seeds)
 267
 268    def __iter__(self):
 269        return iter(self.seeds)
 270
 271    @classmethod
 272    def from_inventory(cls, inventory: Inventory, units: GridUnits = GridUnits.METER) \
 273            -> 'SeedEnsemble':
 274        """
 275        create from an inventory object
 276        :param inventory: an inventory object
 277        :type inventory: uquake.core.inventory.Inventory
 278        :param units: units of measurement used to express x, y, and z
 279        :type units: str must be a valid unit of measurement as defined by the
 280        GridUnits class
 281        :rparam: a Seeds object
 282        """
 283
 284        srces = []
 285        for instrument in inventory.instruments:
 286            srce = Seed(instrument.station_code, instrument.location_code,
 287                        instrument.coordinates)
 288            srces.append(srce)
 289
 290        return cls(srces)
 291
 292    @classmethod
 293    def from_json(cls, json):
 294        pass
 295
 296    def add(self, location: Seed):
 297        """
 298        Add a single location to the source list
 299        :param location:
 300        :type location: Seed
 301        """
 302
 303        self.seeds.append(location)
 304
 305    @classmethod
 306    def generate_random_seeds_in_grid(cls, grid, n_seeds=1):
 307        """
 308        generate n_seeds random seeds inside the grid provided. This function
 309        is mainly used for testing purposes
 310        :param grid: a grid
 311        :type grid: uquake.grid.base.Grid or an object inheriting from Grid
 312        :param n_seeds: number of seeds to generate
 313        :return: a list of seeds
 314
 315        >>> from uquake.grid.base import Grid
 316        >>> from uquake.grid.extended import SeedEnsemble
 317        >>> grid_dimensions = [10, 10, 10]
 318        >>> grid_spacing = [1, 1, 1]
 319        >>> grid_origin = [0, 0, 0]
 320        >>> grid = Grid(grid_dimensions, grid_spacing, grid_origin, value=1)
 321        >>> seeds = SeedEnsemble.generate_random_seeds_in_grid(grid, n_seeds=10)
 322        """
 323
 324        seeds = []
 325        for seed in Seed.random_in_grid(grid, n_seeds=n_seeds):
 326            # import ipdb
 327            # ipdb.set_trace()
 328            seeds.append(seed)
 329
 330        return cls(seeds)
 331
 332    def __repr__(self):
 333        line = ""
 334
 335        divider = 1000 if self.units == GridUnits.KILOMETER else 1
 336
 337        return f'{self.units}\n' + '\n'.join([f'{seed}'
 338                                              for seed in self.seeds])
 339
 340    @property
 341    def nlloc(self):
 342        line = ""
 343
 344        divider = 1000 if self.units == GridUnits.KILOMETER else 1
 345
 346        for seed in self.seeds:
 347            # test if location name is shorter than 6 characters
 348
 349            line += f'GTSRCE {seed.label} XYZ ' \
 350                    f'{seed.x / divider:>15.6f} ' \
 351                    f'{seed.y / divider:>15.6f} ' \
 352                    f'{seed.z / divider:>15.6f} ' \
 353                    f'{seed.elevation:0.2f}\n'
 354
 355        return line
 356
 357    @property
 358    def locs(self):
 359        seeds = []
 360        for location in self.locations:
 361            seeds.append([location['x'], location['y'], location['z']])
 362        return np.array(seeds)
 363
 364    @property
 365    def labels(self):
 366        seed_labels = []
 367        for location in self.locations:
 368            seed_labels.append(location['label'])
 369
 370        return np.array(seed_labels)

 378    def __init__(self, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, phase: Phases,
 379                 value=0, grid_type=GridTypes.VELOCITY_METERS,
 380                 grid_units=__default_grid_units__,
 381                 float_type="FLOAT",
 382                 grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
 383                 label: str = __default_grid_label__,
 384                 coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem = CoordinateSystem.NED):
 385        """
 386        :param data_or_dims: data or data dimensions. If dimensions are
 387        provided a homogeneous grid is created with value=value
 388        :param origin: origin of the grid
 389        :type origin: list
 390        :param spacing: the spacing between grid nodes
 391        :type spacing: list
 392        :param phase: Phase
 393        :type phase: Phases
 394        :param value: a value to fill the grid with if data_or_dims is a list
 395        :type value: float
 396        :param grid_type: grid type
 397        :type grid_type: GridTypes
 398        :param grid_units: grid units
 399        :type grid_units: GridUnits
 400        :param float_type:  the float type either 'FLOAT' or 'DOUBLE'
 401        :type float_type: FloatTypes
 402        :param grid_id: the grid id
 403        :type grid_id: str
 404        :param label: label of the grid
 405        :type label: str
 406        :param coordinate_system: coordinate system either NED or ENU
 407        :type coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem
 408        """
 409
 410        super().__init__(data_or_dims, spacing=spacing, origin=origin,
 411                         value=value, resource_id=grid_id, label=label,
 412                         coordinate_system=coordinate_system)
 413
 414        self.phase = phase
 415        self.grid_type = grid_type
 416        self.grid_units = grid_units
 417        self.float_type = float_type
 418
 419    @property

 421        return self.resource_id

 423    def mv(self, base_name, origin, destination):
 424        """
 425        move a NLLoc grid with a certain base_name from an origin to a
 426        destination
 427        :param NLLocGridObject:
 428        :type NLLocGridObject: uquake.grid.extended.TypedGrid
 429        :param base_name:
 430        :type base_name: str
 431        :param origin:
 432        :type origin: str
 433        :param destination:
 434        :type destination: str
 435        :return:
 436        """
 437
 438        self.write(base_name, destination)
 439        for ext in self.extensions:
 440            shutil.move(f'{origin}/{base_name}.{ext}',
 441                        f'{destination}/{base_name}.{ext}')

 485class LayeredVelocityModel(object):
 486
 487    def __init__(self, network_code: str, velocity_model_layers: List = None,
 488                 phase: Phases = Phases.P,
 489                 grid_units: GridUnits = __default_grid_units__,
 490                 float_type=__default_float_type__,
 491                 gradient=False, grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
 492                 coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem = CoordinateSystem.NED,
 493                 label=__default_grid_label__):
 494        """
 495        Initialize
 496        :param network_code: network code
 497        :type network_code: str
 498        :param velocity_model_layers: a list of VelocityModelLayer
 499        :type velocity_model_layers: list
 500        :param phase: Phase either Phases.P or Phases.S
 501        :type phase: Phases default = Phases.P
 502        :param grid_units: units of measurement used to express x, y, and z
 503        :type grid_units: GridUnits
 504        :param float_type: float type either 'FLOAT' or 'DOUBLE'
 505        :type float_type: FloatTypes default = 'FLOAT'
 506        :param gradient: whether the model is a gradient model or not
 507        (no control layer by layer)
 508        :type gradient: bool default = False
 509        :param grid_id: the grid id
 510        :type grid_id: uquake.core.event.ResourceIdentifier
 511        :param coordinate_system: coordinate system either NED or ENU
 512        :type coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem
 513        :param label: grid label
 514        :type label: str
 515        """
 516
 517        self.network_code = network_code
 518
 519        if velocity_model_layers is None:
 520            self.velocity_model_layers = []
 521
 522        if isinstance(phase, Phases):
 523            self.phase = phase
 524        elif isinstance(phase, str):
 525            self.phase = Phases(phase)
 526        else:
 527            raise TypeError('phase must be a Phases object')
 528
 529        if isinstance(grid_units, GridUnits):
 530            self.grid_units = grid_units
 531        elif isinstance(grid_units, str):
 532            self.grid_units = GridUnits(grid_units)
 533        else:
 534            raise TypeError('grid_units must be a GridUnits object')
 535
 536        if isinstance(float_type, FloatTypes):
 537            self.float_type = float_type
 538        elif isinstance(float_type, str):
 539            self.float_type = FloatTypes(float_type)
 540        else:
 541            raise TypeError('float_type must be a FloatTypes object')
 542
 543        self.grid_type = GridTypes.VELOCITY_METERS
 544
 545        self.grid_id = grid_id
 546
 547        self.gradient = gradient
 548        self.coordinate_system = coordinate_system
 549        self.label = label
 550
 551    def __repr__(self):
 552        output = ''
 553        for i, layer in enumerate(self.velocity_model_layers):
 554            output += f'layer {i + 1:4d} | {layer}'
 555
 556        return output
 557
 558    def add_layer(self, layer: ModelLayer):
 559        """
 560        Add a layer to the model. The layers must be added in sequence from the
 561        top to the bottom
 562        :param layer: a ModelLayer object
 563        """
 564        if not (type(layer) is ModelLayer):
 565            raise TypeError('layer must be a VelocityModelLayer object')
 566
 567        if self.velocity_model_layers is None:
 568            self.velocity_model_layers = [layer]
 569        else:
 570            self.velocity_model_layers.append(layer)
 571
 572    def to_1d_model(self, z_min, z_max, spacing):
 573        # sort the layers to ensure the layers are properly ordered
 574        z = []
 575        v = []
 576        for layer in self.velocity_model_layers:
 577            z.append(layer.z_top)
 578            v.append(layer.value_top)
 579
 580        if np.max(z) < z_max:
 581            i_z_max = np.argmax(z)
 582            v_z_max = v[i_z_max]
 583
 584            z.append(z_max)
 585            v.append(v_z_max)
 586
 587        if np.min(z) > z_min:
 588            i_z_min = np.argmin(z)
 589            v_z_min = v[i_z_min]
 590
 591            z.append(z_min)
 592            v.append(v_z_min)
 593
 594        i_sort = np.argsort(z)
 595
 596        z = np.array(z)
 597        v = np.array(v)
 598
 599        z = z[i_sort]
 600        v = v[i_sort]
 601
 602        z_interp = np.arange(z_min, z_max, spacing)
 603        kind = 'previous'
 604        if self.gradient:
 605            kind = 'linear'
 606
 607        f_interp = interp1d(z, v, kind=kind)
 608
 609        v_interp = f_interp(z_interp)
 610
 611        return z_interp, v_interp
 612
 613    def to_3d_grid(self, dims, origin, spacing):
 614        model_grid_3d = VelocityGrid3D.from_layered_model(self, dims, origin,
 615                                                          spacing, label=self.label)
 616        return model_grid_3d
 617
 618    def plot(self, z_min, z_max, spacing, invert_z_axis=True, *args, **kwargs):
 619        """
 620        Plot the 1D velocity model
 621        :param z_min: lower limit of the model
 622        :param z_max: upper limit of the model
 623        :param spacing: plotting resolution in z
 624        :param invert_z_axis: whether the z axis is inverted or not
 625        (default = True)
 626        :return: matplotlib axis
 627        """
 628
 629        z_interp, v_interp = self.to_1d_model(z_min, z_max, spacing)
 630
 631        x_label = None
 632        if self.phase == 'P':
 633            x_label = 'P-wave velocity'
 634        elif self.phase == 'S':
 635            x_label = 's-wave velocity'
 636
 637        if self.grid_units == 'METER':
 638            units = 'm'
 639        else:
 640            units = 'km'
 641
 642        y_label = f'z [{units}]'
 643        ax = plt.axes()
 644        ax.plot(v_interp, z_interp, *args, **kwargs)
 645        plt.xlabel(x_label)
 646        plt.ylabel(y_label)
 647
 648        if invert_z_axis:
 649            ax.invert_yaxis()
 650
 651        ax.set_aspect(2)
 652
 653        plt.tight_layout()
 654
 655        return ax

 765    def to_time(self, seed: Seed, sub_grid_resolution=0.1,
 766                *args, **kwargs):
 767        """
 768        Eikonal solver based on scikit fast marching solver
 769        :param seed: numpy array location of the seed or origin of useis wave
 770         in model coordinates
 771        (usually location of a station or an event)
 772        :type seed: numpy.ndarray or list
 773        :param sub_grid_resolution: resolution of the grid around the seed.
 774        Propagating the wavefront on a denser grid around the seed,
 775        significantly improves the travel time accuracy. The value represents
 776        a fraction of the grid resolution. For instance, assuming a grid with
 777        spacing of 10m, if the sub_grid_resolution is set to 0.1, the
 778        resolution around the grid will be 1m.
 779
 780        :rtype: TTGrid
 781        """
 782
 783        if isinstance(seed, list):
 784            seed = np.array(seed)
 785
 786        if not self.in_grid(seed.loc):
 787            logger.warning(f'{seed.label} is outside the grid. '
 788                           f'The travel time grid will not be calculated')
 789            return
 790
 791        origin = self.origin
 792        shape = self.shape
 793        spacing = self.spacing
 794
 795        sub_grid_spacing = spacing * sub_grid_resolution
 796
 797        # extent = ((4 * sub_grid_spacing) * 1.2 + sub_grid_spacing)
 798
 799        n_pts_inner_grid = (4 * spacing / sub_grid_spacing * 1.2).astype(int)
 800        for i in range(0, len(n_pts_inner_grid)):
 801            if n_pts_inner_grid[i] % 2:
 802                n_pts_inner_grid[i] += 1
 803
 804        x_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[0]) * sub_grid_spacing[0]
 805        y_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[1]) * sub_grid_spacing[1]
 806        z_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[2]) * sub_grid_spacing[2]
 807
 808        x_i = x_i - np.mean(x_i) + seed.x
 809        y_i = y_i - np.mean(y_i) + seed.y
 810        z_i = z_i - np.mean(z_i) + seed.z
 811
 812        X_i, Y_i, Z_i = np.meshgrid(x_i, y_i, z_i, indexing='ij')
 813
 814        coords = np.array([X_i.ravel(), Y_i.ravel(), Z_i.ravel()]).T
 815
 816        vel = self.interpolate(coords, grid_space=False).reshape(
 817            X_i.shape)
 818
 819        phi = np.ones_like(X_i)
 820        phi[int(np.floor(len(x_i) / 2)), int(np.floor(len(y_i) / 2)),
 821            int(np.floor(len(z_i) / 2))] = 0
 822
 823        tt_tmp = skfmm.travel_time(phi, vel, dx=sub_grid_spacing)
 824
 825        tt_tmp_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_tmp, [x_i[0], y_i[0], z_i[0]],
 826                             sub_grid_spacing, seed, self.grid_id,
 827                             phase=self.phase,
 828                             float_type=self.float_type, label=self.label)
 829
 830        # __init__(self, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, seed: Seed,
 831        # phase: Phases = Phases.P, value: float = 0,
 832        # float_type: FloatTypes = __default_float_type__,
 833        # grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
 834        # grid_units: GridUnits = __default_grid_units__):
 835
 836        data = self.data
 837
 838        xe = origin[0] + np.arange(0, shape[0], 1) * spacing[0]
 839        ye = origin[1] + np.arange(0, shape[1], 1) * spacing[1]
 840        ze = origin[2] + np.arange(0, shape[2], 1) * spacing[2]
 841
 842        Xe, Ye, Ze = np.meshgrid(xe, ye, ze, indexing='ij')
 843
 844        coords = np.array([Xe.ravel(), Ye.ravel(), Ze.ravel()])
 845
 846        corner1 = np.array([np.min(x_i), np.min(y_i), np.min(z_i)])
 847        corner2 = np.array([np.max(x_i), np.max(y_i), np.max(z_i)])
 848
 849        test = ((coords[0, :] >= corner1[0]) & (coords[0, :] <= corner2[0]) &
 850                (coords[1, :] >= corner1[1]) & (coords[1, :] <= corner2[1]) &
 851                (coords[2, :] >= corner1[2]) & (coords[2, :] <= corner2[2]))
 852
 853        Xe_grid = Xe.ravel()[test]
 854        Ye_grid = Ye.ravel()[test]
 855        Ze_grid = Ze.ravel()[test]
 856
 857        X = np.array([Xe_grid, Ye_grid, Ze_grid]).T
 858
 859        tt_interp = tt_tmp_grid.interpolate(X, grid_space=False,
 860                                            order=3)[0]
 861
 862        bias = np.max(tt_interp)
 863
 864        phi_out = np.ones_like(Xe).ravel()
 865        phi_out[test] = tt_interp - bias
 866
 867        phi_out = phi_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
 868
 869        tt_out = skfmm.travel_time(phi_out, data, dx=spacing)
 870
 871        # tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
 872        tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
 873        tt_out[test] = tt_interp
 874        tt_out = tt_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
 875
 876        tt_out_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_out, self.origin,
 877                             self.spacing, seed, phase=self.phase,
 878                             float_type=self.float_type,
 879                             velocity_model_id=self.grid_id,
 880                             label=self.label)
 881
 882        tt_out_grid.data -= tt_out_grid.interpolate(seed.T,
 883                                                    grid_space=False,
 884                                                    order=3)[0]
 885
 886        return tt_out_grid
 887
 888    def to_time_multi_threaded(self, seeds: SeedEnsemble, cpu_utilisation=0.9,
 889                               *args, **kwargs):
 890        """
 891        Multithreaded version of the Eikonal solver
 892        based on scikit fast marching solver
 893        :param seeds: array of seed
 894        :type seeds: np.ndarray
 895        :param cpu_utilisation: fraction of the cpu core to be used for the
 896        processing task (between 0 and 1)
 897        :type cpu_utilisation: float between 0 and 1
 898        :param args: arguments to be passed directly to skfmm.travel_time
 899        function
 900        :param kwargs: keyword arguments to be passed directly to
 901        skfmm.travel_time function
 902        :return: a travel time grid ensemble
 903        :rtype: TravelTimeEnsemble
 904        """
 905
 906        num_threads = int(np.ceil(cpu_utilisation * __cpu_count__))
 907        # ensuring that the number of threads is comprised between 1 and
 908        # __cpu_count__
 909        num_threads = np.max([np.min([num_threads, __cpu_count__]), 1])
 910
 911        data = []
 912        for seed in seeds:
 913            if not self.in_grid(seed.loc):
 914                logger.warning(f'{seed.label} is outside the grid. '
 915                               f'The travel time grid will not be calculated')
 916                continue
 917
 918        with Pool(num_threads) as pool:
 919            results = pool.map(self.to_time, seeds)
 920
 921        tt_grid_ensemble = TravelTimeEnsemble(results)
 922
 923        return tt_grid_ensemble

 946class VelocityGridEnsemble:
 947    def __init__(self, p_velocity_grid, s_velocity_grid):
 948        """
 949
 950        :param p_velocity_grid: p-wave 3D velocity grid
 951        :type p_velocity_grid: VelocityGrid3D
 952        :param s_velocity_grid: s-wave 3D velocity grid
 953        :type s_velocity_grid: VelocityGrid3D
 954
 955        :NOTE: the p and s velocity grids must have the same dimensions and the same
 956        label
 957        """
 958
 959        if p_velocity_grid.dims != s_velocity_grid.dims:
 960            raise ValueError('p and s velocity grids must have the same '
 961                             'dimensions')
 962        if p_velocity_grid.label != s_velocity_grid.label:
 963            raise ValueError('p and s velocity grids must have the same '
 964                             'label')
 965
 966        self.p_velocity_grid = p_velocity_grid
 967        self.s_velocity_grid = s_velocity_grid
 968        self.label = p_velocity_grid.label
 969        self.__i__ = 0
 970
 971    def __getitem__(self, item):
 972        if item.upper() == 'P':
 973            return self.p_velocity_grid
 974
 975        elif item.upper() == 'S':
 976            return self.s_velocity_grid
 977
 978        else:
 979            raise ValueError(f'{item} is not a valid key. '
 980                             f'The key value must either be "P" or "S"')
 981
 982    def __iter__(self):
 983        self.__i__ = 0
 984        return self
 985
 986    def __next__(self):
 987        if self.__i__ < 2:
 988            if self.__i__ == '0':
 989                return self.p_velocity_grid
 990            elif self.__i__ == '1':
 991                return self.s_velocity_grid
 992        else:
 993            raise StopIteration
 994
 995    @staticmethod
 996    def keys():
 997        return ['P', 'S']
 998
 999    def write(self, path='.'):
1000        for key in self.keys():
1001            self[key].write(path=path)
1002
1003    def to_time_multi_threaded(self, seeds: SeedEnsemble, cpu_utilisation=0.9,
1004                               *args, **kwargs):
1005        """
1006        Multithreaded version of the Eikonal solver
1007        :param seeds:
1008        :param cpu_utilisation:
1009        :param args:
1010        :param kwargs:
1011        :return:
1012        """
1013
1014        tt_grid_ensemble = TravelTimeEnsemble([])
1015
1016        for key in self.keys():
1017            tt_grids = self[key].to_time_multi_threaded(seeds,
1018                                                        cpu_utilisation=
1019                                                        cpu_utilisation,
1020                                                        *args, **kwargs)
1021
1022            tt_grid_ensemble += tt_grids
1023
1024        return tt_grid_ensemble
1025
1026    def to_time(self, seeds: SeedEnsemble, multi_threaded=False, *args, **kwargs):
1027        if multi_threaded:
1028            return self.to_time_multi_threaded(seeds)
1029
1030        else:
1031            tt_grid_ensemble = TravelTimeEnsemble([])
1032            for key in self.keys():
1033                for seed in zip(seeds):
1034                    tt_grid_ensemble += self[key].to_time(seed)

1078        :param network: network code

1080        If dimensions not provided a grid with value=value is created
1081        :param origin: origin of the grid
1082        :param spacing: the spacing between grid nodes
1083        :param seed: seed location of the grid - The seed or instrument location
1084        :param velocity_model_id: velocity model id
1085        :param phase: Seismic Phase
1086        :param value: value of the grid when only specifying the dimensions
1087        :param grid_units: units of measurement used to express values
1088        :param grid_type: type of grid (e.g., travel time, azimuth, take off angle)
1089        :param float_type: float type either 'FLOAT' or 'DOUBLE'
1090        :param grid_id: the grid id
1091        :param label: label of the grid
1092        :param coordinate_system: coordinate system either NED or ENU
1093        """
1094
1095        self.network = network_code
1096        self.seed = seed
1097        self.velocity_model_id = velocity_model_id
1098
1099        self.seed_label = seed.label
1100
1101        if isinstance(grid_type, str):
1102            self.grid_type = SeededGridType(grid_type)
1103        elif isinstance(grid_type, SeededGridType):
1104            self.grid_type = grid_type
1105        elif isinstance(grid_type, GridTypes):
1106            self.grid_type = SeededGridType(grid_type.value)
1107        else:
1108            raise TypeError('grid_type must be a SeededGridType object')
1109
1110        super().__init__(data_or_dims, origin, spacing,
1111                         phase=phase, value=value,
1112                         grid_type=grid_type, grid_units=grid_units,
1113                         float_type=float_type, grid_id=grid_id, label=label,
1114                         coordinate_system=coordinate_system)
1115
1116        # ensure the data are expressed in the appropriate float_type
1117        self.data.astype(float_type.value)

1168class TTGrid(SeededGrid):
1169    def __init__(self, network_code, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, seed: Seed,
1170                 velocity_model_id: ResourceIdentifier,
1171                 phase: Phases = Phases.P, value: float = 0,
1172                 float_type: FloatTypes = __default_float_type__,
1173                 grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
1174                 label=__default_grid_label__,
1175                 coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem = CoordinateSystem.NED):
1176
1177        super().__init__(network_code, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, seed,
1178                         velocity_model_id=velocity_model_id, phase=phase,
1179                         value=value, grid_type=GridTypes.TIME,
1180                         grid_units=GridUnits.SECOND,
1181                         float_type=float_type,
1182                         grid_id=grid_id,
1183                         coordinate_system = coordinate_system,
1184                         label=label)
1185
1186    def to_azimuth(self):
1187        """
1188        This function calculate the takeoff angle and azimuth for every
1189        grid point given a travel time grid calculated using an Eikonal solver
1190        :return: azimuth and takeoff angles grids
1191        .. Note: The convention for the takeoff angle is that 0 degree is down.
1192        """
1193
1194        gds_tmp = np.gradient(self.data)
1195        gds = [-gd for gd in gds_tmp]
1196
1197        azimuth = np.arctan2(gds[0], gds[1]) * 180 / np.pi
1198        # azimuth is zero northwards
1199
1200        return AngleGrid(self.waveform_id, azimuth, self.origin, self.spacing,
1201                         'AZIMUTH', self.seed, seed_label=self.seed_label,
1202                         phase=self.phase, float_type=self.float_type,
1203                         model_id=ResourceIdentifier(), grid_units=GridUnits.DEGREE)
1204
1205    def to_takeoff(self):
1206        gds_tmp = np.gradient(self.data)
1207        gds = [-gd for gd in gds_tmp]
1208
1209        hor = np.sqrt(gds[0] ** 2 + gds[1] ** 2)
1210        takeoff = np.arctan2(hor, -gds[2]) * 180 / np.pi
1211        # takeoff is zero pointing down
1212        return AngleGrid(self.network_code, takeoff, self.origin, self.spacing,
1213                         'TAKEOFF', self.seed, seed_label=self.seed_label,
1214                         phase=self.phase, float_type=self.float_type,
1215                         model_id=self.model_id, grid_units=self.grid_units)
1216
1217    def to_azimuth_point(self, coord, grid_space=False, mode='nearest',
1218                         order=1, **kwargs):
1219        """
1220        calculate the azimuth angle at a particular point on the grid for a
1221        given seed location
1222        :param coord: coordinates at which to calculate the takeoff angle
1223        :param grid_space: true if the coordinates are expressed in
1224        grid space (indices can be fractional) as opposed to model space
1225        (x, y, z)
1226        :param mode: interpolation mode
1227        :param order: interpolation order
1228        :return: takeoff angle at the location coord
1229        """
1230
1231        return self.to_azimuth().interpolate(coord,
1232                                             grid_space=grid_space,
1233                                             mode=mode, order=order,
1234                                             **kwargs)[0]

1288class TravelTimeEnsemble:
1289    def __init__(self, travel_time_grids):
1290        """
1291        Combine a list of travel time grids together providing meta
1292        functionality (multithreaded ray tracing, sorting, travel-time
1293        calculation for a specific location etc.). It is assumed that
1294        all grids are compatible, i.e., that all the grids have the same
1295        origin, spacing and dimensions.
1296        :param travel_time_grids: a list of TTGrid objects
1297
1298        :NOTE: The travel time grids must all have the same grid labels if not,
1299        the object will not be created.
1300        """
1301
1302        self.travel_time_grids = []
1303        for travel_time_grid in travel_time_grids:
1304            if travel_time_grid.label != travel_time_grids[0].label:
1305                raise ValueError('all travel time grids must have the same '
1306                                 'label')
1307            self.travel_time_grids.append(travel_time_grid)
1308
1309        self.__i__ = 0
1310
1311        for tt_grid in self.travel_time_grids:
1312            try:
1313                assert tt_grid.check_compatibility(travel_time_grids[0])
1314            except:
1315                raise AssertionError('grids are not all compatible')
1316
1317    def __len__(self):
1318        return len(self.travel_time_grids)
1319
1320    def __add__(self, other):
1321        for travel_time_grid in other.travel_time_grids:
1322            self.travel_time_grids.append(travel_time_grid)
1323
1324        return TravelTimeEnsemble(self.travel_time_grids)
1325
1326    def __iter__(self):
1327        self.__i__ = 0
1328        return self
1329
1330    def __next__(self):
1331        if self.__i__ < len(self):
1332            result = self.travel_time_grids[self.__i__]
1333            self.__i__ += 1
1334            return result
1335        else:
1336            raise StopIteration
1337
1338    def __getitem__(self, item):
1339        if isinstance(item, int):
1340            return self.travel_time_grids[item]
1341        if isinstance(item, str):
1342            for tt_grid in self.travel_time_grids:
1343                if tt_grid.seed_label == item:
1344                    return tt_grid
1345
1346    def __repr__(self):
1347        line = f'Number of travel time grids: {len(self)}'
1348        return line

1350    @classmethod
1351    def from_files(cls, path):
1352        """
1353        create a travel time ensemble from files located in a directory
1354        :param path: the base path to the directory containing the travel time
1355        files.
1356        :return:
1357        """
1358        tt_grids = []
1359        for fle in Path(path).glob('*time*.hdr'):
1360            path = fle.parent
1361            base_name = '.'.join(fle.name.split('.')[:-1])
1362            fname = str(Path(path) / base_name)
1363            tt_grid = read_grid(fname, format='NLLOC',
1364                                float_type=__default_float_type__)
1365            tt_grids.append(tt_grid)
1366
1367        return cls(tt_grids)

1369    def select(self, seed_labels: Optional[List[str]] = None,
1370               phases: Optional[List[Phases]] = None):
1371        """
1372        return a list of grid corresponding to seed_labels.
1373        :param seed_labels: seed labels of the travel time grids to return
1374        :param phases: the phase {'P' or 'S'}, both if None.
1375        :return: a list of travel time grids
1376        :rtype: TravelTimeEnsemble
1377        """
1378
1379        if (seed_labels is None) and (phases is None):
1380            return self
1381
1382        tmp = []
1383        if seed_labels is None:
1384            seed_labels = np.unique(self.seed_labels)
1385
1386        if phases is None:
1387            phases = [Phases.P.value, Phases.S.value]
1388        else:
1389            phases = [phase.value if isinstance(phase, Phases) else Phases(phase).value
1390                      for phase in phases]
1391
1392        returned_grids = []
1393        for travel_time_grid in self.travel_time_grids:
1394            if travel_time_grid.seed_label in seed_labels:
1395                if travel_time_grid.phase.value in phases:
1396                    returned_grids.append(travel_time_grid)
1397
1398        return TravelTimeEnsemble(returned_grids)

1400    def sort(self, ascending: bool = True):
1401        """
1402        sorting the travel time grid by seed_label
1403        :param ascending: if true the grids are sorted in ascending order
1404        :param ascending: bool
1405        :return: sorted travel time grids.
1406        :rtype: TravelTimeEnsemble
1407        """
1408
1409        i = np.sort(self.seed_labels)
1410
1411        if not ascending:
1412            i = i[-1::-1]

1414        sorted_tt_grids = np.array(self.travel_time_grids)[i]

1418    def travel_time(self, seed, grid_space: bool = False,
1419                    seed_labels: Optional[list] = None,
1420                    phase: Optional[list] = None):
1421        """
1422        calculate the travel time at a specific point for a series of location
1423        ids
1424        :param seed: travel time seed
1425        :param grid_space: true if the coordinates are expressed in
1426        grid space (indices can be fractional) as opposed to model space
1427        (x, y, z)
1428        :param seed_labels: a list of locations from which to calculate the
1429        travel time.
1430        :param phase: a list of phases for which the travel time need to be
1431        calculated
1432        :return: a list of dictionary containing the travel time and location id
1433        """
1434
1435        if isinstance(seed, list):
1436            seed = np.array(seed)
1437
1438        if grid_space:
1439            seed = self.travel_time_grids[0].transform_from(seed)
1440
1441        if not self.travel_time_grids[0].in_grid(seed):
1442            raise ValueError('seed is outside the grid')
1443
1444        tt_grids = self.select(seed_labels=seed_labels, phase=phase)
1445
1446        tts = []
1447        labels = []
1448        phases = []
1449        for tt_grid in tt_grids:
1450            labels.append(tt_grid.seed_label)
1451            tts.append(tt_grid.interpolate(seed.T,
1452                       grid_space=False)[0])
1453            phases.append(tt_grid.phase)
1454
1455        tts_dict = {}
1456        for phase in np.unique(phases):
1457            tts_dict[phase] = {}
1458
1459        for label, tt, phase in zip(labels, tts, phases):
1460            tts_dict[phase][label] = tt
1461
1462        return tts_dict
1463
1464    def angles(self, seed, grid_space: bool = False,
1465                seed_labels: Optional[list] = None,
1466                phase: Optional[list] = None, **kwargs):
1467        """
1468        calculate the azimuth at a specific point for a series of location
1469        ids
1470        :param seed: travel time seed
1471        :param grid_space: true if the coordinates are expressed in
1472        grid space (indices can be fractional) as opposed to model space
1473        (x, y, z)
1474        :param seed_labels: a list of locations from which to calculate the
1475        travel time.
1476        :param phase: a list of phases for which the travel time need to be
1477        calculated
1478        :return: a list of dictionary containing the azimuth and location id
1479        """
1480
1481        if isinstance(seed, list):
1482            seed = np.array(seed)
1483
1484        if grid_space:
1485            seed = self.travel_time_grids[0].transform_from(seed)
1486
1487        if not self.travel_time_grids[0].in_grid(seed):
1488            raise ValueError('seed is outside the grid')
1489
1490        tt_grids = self.select(seed_labels=seed_labels, phase=phase)
1491
1492        azimuths = []
1493        takeoffs = []
1494        labels = []
1495        phases = []
1496        for tt_grid in tt_grids:
1497            labels.append(tt_grid.seed_label)
1498            azimuths.append(tt_grid.to_azimuth_point(seed.T,
1499                                                     grid_space=False,
1500                                                     **kwargs))
1501            takeoffs.append(tt_grid.to_takeoff_point(seed.T,
1502                                                     grid_space=False,
1503                                                     **kwargs))
1504            phases.append(tt_grid.phase)
1505
1506        azimuth_dict = {}
1507        takeoff_dict = {}
1508        for phase in np.unique(phases):
1509            azimuth_dict[phase] = {}
1510            takeoff_dict[phase] = {}
1511
1512        for label, azimuth, takeoff, phase in zip(labels, azimuths, takeoffs,
1513                                                  phases):
1514            takeoff_dict[phase][label] = takeoff
1515            azimuth_dict[phase][label] = azimuth
1516
1517        angle_dict = {}
1518        angle_dict['takeoff'] = takeoff_dict
1519        angle_dict['azimuth'] = azimuth_dict
1520
1521        return angle_dict
1522
1523    def ray_tracer(self, starts, seed_label=None, multithreading=False,
1524                   cpu_utilisation=0.9, grid_space=False, max_iter=1000):
1525        """
1526
1527        :param starts: origin of the ray, usually the location of the events
1528        :param seed_label: a list of seed labels
1529        :param grid_space: true if the coordinates are expressed in
1530        grid space (indices can be fractional) as opposed to model space
1531        (x, y, z)
1532        :param multithreading: if True use multithreading
1533        :param max_iter: maximum number of iteration
1534        :param cpu_utilisation: fraction of core to use, between 0 and 1.
1535        The number of core to be use is bound between 1 and the total number of
1536        cores
1537        :return: a list of rays
1538        :rtype: list
1539        """
1540
1541        travel_time_grid = self.select(seed_labels=[seed_label])
1542
1543        kwargs = {'grid_space': grid_space,
1544                  'max_iter': max_iter}
1545
1546        if multithreading:
1547
1548            ray_tracer_func = partial(ray_tracer, **kwargs)
1549
1550            num_threads = int(np.ceil(cpu_utilisation * __cpu_count__))
1551            # ensuring that the number of threads is comprised between 1 and
1552            # __cpu_count__
1553            num_threads = np.max([np.min([num_threads, __cpu_count__]), 1])
1554
1555            data = []
1556            for start in starts:
1557                data.append((travel_time_grid, start))
1558
1559            with Pool(num_threads) as pool:
1560                results = pool.starmap(ray_tracer_func, data)
1561
1562            for result in results:
1563                result.network = self.travel_time_grids[0].network_code
1564
1565        else:
1566            results = []
1567            for start in starts:
1568                results.append(travel_time_grid.ray_tracer(start, **kwargs))
1569
1570        return results

486class LayeredVelocityModel(object):

488    def __init__(self, network_code: str, velocity_model_layers: List = None,
489                 phase: Phases = Phases.P,
490                 grid_units: GridUnits = __default_grid_units__,
491                 float_type=__default_float_type__,
492                 gradient=False, grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
493                 coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem = CoordinateSystem.NED,
494                 label=__default_grid_label__):
495        """
496        Initialize
497        :param network_code: network code
498        :type network_code: str
499        :param velocity_model_layers: a list of VelocityModelLayer
500        :type velocity_model_layers: list
501        :param phase: Phase either Phases.P or Phases.S
502        :type phase: Phases default = Phases.P
503        :param grid_units: units of measurement used to express x, y, and z
504        :type grid_units: GridUnits
505        :param float_type: float type either 'FLOAT' or 'DOUBLE'
506        :type float_type: FloatTypes default = 'FLOAT'
507        :param gradient: whether the model is a gradient model or not
508        (no control layer by layer)
509        :type gradient: bool default = False
510        :param grid_id: the grid id
511        :type grid_id: uquake.core.event.ResourceIdentifier
512        :param coordinate_system: coordinate system either NED or ENU
513        :type coordinate_system: CoordinateSystem
514        :param label: grid label
515        :type label: str
516        """
517
518        self.network_code = network_code
519
520        if velocity_model_layers is None:
521            self.velocity_model_layers = []
522
523        if isinstance(phase, Phases):
524            self.phase = phase
525        elif isinstance(phase, str):
526            self.phase = Phases(phase)
527        else:
528            raise TypeError('phase must be a Phases object')
529
530        if isinstance(grid_units, GridUnits):
531            self.grid_units = grid_units
532        elif isinstance(grid_units, str):
533            self.grid_units = GridUnits(grid_units)
534        else:
535            raise TypeError('grid_units must be a GridUnits object')
536
537        if isinstance(float_type, FloatTypes):
538            self.float_type = float_type
539        elif isinstance(float_type, str):
540            self.float_type = FloatTypes(float_type)
541        else:
542            raise TypeError('float_type must be a FloatTypes object')
543
544        self.grid_type = GridTypes.VELOCITY_METERS
545
546        self.grid_id = grid_id
547
548        self.gradient = gradient
549        self.coordinate_system = coordinate_system
550        self.label = label
551
552    def __repr__(self):
553        output = ''
554        for i, layer in enumerate(self.velocity_model_layers):
555            output += f'layer {i + 1:4d} | {layer}'
556
557        return output
558
559    def add_layer(self, layer: ModelLayer):
560        """
561        Add a layer to the model. The layers must be added in sequence from the
562        top to the bottom
563        :param layer: a ModelLayer object
564        """
565        if not (type(layer) is ModelLayer):
566            raise TypeError('layer must be a VelocityModelLayer object')
567
568        if self.velocity_model_layers is None:
569            self.velocity_model_layers = [layer]
570        else:
571            self.velocity_model_layers.append(layer)
572
573    def to_1d_model(self, z_min, z_max, spacing):
574        # sort the layers to ensure the layers are properly ordered
575        z = []
576        v = []
577        for layer in self.velocity_model_layers:
578            z.append(layer.z_top)
579            v.append(layer.value_top)
580
581        if np.max(z) < z_max:
582            i_z_max = np.argmax(z)
583            v_z_max = v[i_z_max]
584
585            z.append(z_max)
586            v.append(v_z_max)
587
588        if np.min(z) > z_min:
589            i_z_min = np.argmin(z)
590            v_z_min = v[i_z_min]
591
592            z.append(z_min)
593            v.append(v_z_min)
594
595        i_sort = np.argsort(z)
596
597        z = np.array(z)
598        v = np.array(v)
599
600        z = z[i_sort]
601        v = v[i_sort]
602
603        z_interp = np.arange(z_min, z_max, spacing)
604        kind = 'previous'
605        if self.gradient:
606            kind = 'linear'
607
608        f_interp = interp1d(z, v, kind=kind)
609
610        v_interp = f_interp(z_interp)
611
612        return z_interp, v_interp
613
614    def to_3d_grid(self, dims, origin, spacing):
615        model_grid_3d = VelocityGrid3D.from_layered_model(self, dims, origin,
616                                                          spacing, label=self.label)
617        return model_grid_3d

619    def plot(self, z_min, z_max, spacing, invert_z_axis=True, *args, **kwargs):
620        """
621        Plot the 1D velocity model
622        :param z_min: lower limit of the model
623        :param z_max: upper limit of the model
624        :param spacing: plotting resolution in z
625        :param invert_z_axis: whether the z axis is inverted or not
626        (default = True)
627        :return: matplotlib axis
628        """
629
630        z_interp, v_interp = self.to_1d_model(z_min, z_max, spacing)
631
632        x_label = None
633        if self.phase == 'P':
634            x_label = 'P-wave velocity'
635        elif self.phase == 'S':
636            x_label = 's-wave velocity'
637
638        if self.grid_units == 'METER':
639            units = 'm'
640        else:
641            units = 'km'
642
643        y_label = f'z [{units}]'
644        ax = plt.axes()
645        ax.plot(v_interp, z_interp, *args, **kwargs)
646        plt.xlabel(x_label)
647        plt.ylabel(y_label)
648
649        if invert_z_axis:
650            ax.invert_yaxis()
651
652        ax.set_aspect(2)
653
654        plt.tight_layout()

def to_1d_model(self, z_min, z_max, spacing): 
573    def to_1d_model(self, z_min, z_max, spacing):
574        # sort the layers to ensure the layers are properly ordered
575        z = []
576        v = []
577        for layer in self.velocity_model_layers:
578            z.append(layer.z_top)
579            v.append(layer.value_top)
580
581        if np.max(z) < z_max:
582            i_z_max = np.argmax(z)
583            v_z_max = v[i_z_max]
584
585            z.append(z_max)
586            v.append(v_z_max)
587
588        if np.min(z) > z_min:
589            i_z_min = np.argmin(z)
590            v_z_min = v[i_z_min]
591
592            z.append(z_min)
593            v.append(v_z_min)
594
595        i_sort = np.argsort(z)
596
597        z = np.array(z)
598        v = np.array(v)
599
600        z = z[i_sort]
601        v = v[i_sort]
602
603        z_interp = np.arange(z_min, z_max, spacing)
604        kind = 'previous'
605        if self.gradient:
606            kind = 'linear'
607
608        f_interp = interp1d(z, v, kind=kind)
609
610        v_interp = f_interp(z_interp)
611
612        return z_interp, v_interp

766    def to_time(self, seed: Seed, sub_grid_resolution=0.1,
767                *args, **kwargs):
768        """
769        Eikonal solver based on scikit fast marching solver
770        :param seed: numpy array location of the seed or origin of useis wave
771         in model coordinates
772        (usually location of a station or an event)
773        :type seed: numpy.ndarray or list
774        :param sub_grid_resolution: resolution of the grid around the seed.
775        Propagating the wavefront on a denser grid around the seed,
776        significantly improves the travel time accuracy. The value represents
777        a fraction of the grid resolution. For instance, assuming a grid with
778        spacing of 10m, if the sub_grid_resolution is set to 0.1, the
779        resolution around the grid will be 1m.
780
781        :rtype: TTGrid
782        """
783
784        if isinstance(seed, list):
785            seed = np.array(seed)
786
787        if not self.in_grid(seed.loc):
788            logger.warning(f'{seed.label} is outside the grid. '
789                           f'The travel time grid will not be calculated')
790            return
791
792        origin = self.origin
793        shape = self.shape
794        spacing = self.spacing
795
796        sub_grid_spacing = spacing * sub_grid_resolution
797
798        # extent = ((4 * sub_grid_spacing) * 1.2 + sub_grid_spacing)
799
800        n_pts_inner_grid = (4 * spacing / sub_grid_spacing * 1.2).astype(int)
801        for i in range(0, len(n_pts_inner_grid)):
802            if n_pts_inner_grid[i] % 2:
803                n_pts_inner_grid[i] += 1
804
805        x_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[0]) * sub_grid_spacing[0]
806        y_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[1]) * sub_grid_spacing[1]
807        z_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[2]) * sub_grid_spacing[2]
808
809        x_i = x_i - np.mean(x_i) + seed.x
810        y_i = y_i - np.mean(y_i) + seed.y
811        z_i = z_i - np.mean(z_i) + seed.z
812
813        X_i, Y_i, Z_i = np.meshgrid(x_i, y_i, z_i, indexing='ij')
814
815        coords = np.array([X_i.ravel(), Y_i.ravel(), Z_i.ravel()]).T
816
817        vel = self.interpolate(coords, grid_space=False).reshape(
818            X_i.shape)
819
820        phi = np.ones_like(X_i)
821        phi[int(np.floor(len(x_i) / 2)), int(np.floor(len(y_i) / 2)),
822            int(np.floor(len(z_i) / 2))] = 0
823
824        tt_tmp = skfmm.travel_time(phi, vel, dx=sub_grid_spacing)
825
826        tt_tmp_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_tmp, [x_i[0], y_i[0], z_i[0]],
827                             sub_grid_spacing, seed, self.grid_id,
828                             phase=self.phase,
829                             float_type=self.float_type, label=self.label)
830
831        # __init__(self, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, seed: Seed,
832        # phase: Phases = Phases.P, value: float = 0,
833        # float_type: FloatTypes = __default_float_type__,
834        # grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
835        # grid_units: GridUnits = __default_grid_units__):
836
837        data = self.data
838
839        xe = origin[0] + np.arange(0, shape[0], 1) * spacing[0]
840        ye = origin[1] + np.arange(0, shape[1], 1) * spacing[1]
841        ze = origin[2] + np.arange(0, shape[2], 1) * spacing[2]
842
843        Xe, Ye, Ze = np.meshgrid(xe, ye, ze, indexing='ij')
844
845        coords = np.array([Xe.ravel(), Ye.ravel(), Ze.ravel()])
846
847        corner1 = np.array([np.min(x_i), np.min(y_i), np.min(z_i)])
848        corner2 = np.array([np.max(x_i), np.max(y_i), np.max(z_i)])
849
850        test = ((coords[0, :] >= corner1[0]) & (coords[0, :] <= corner2[0]) &
851                (coords[1, :] >= corner1[1]) & (coords[1, :] <= corner2[1]) &
852                (coords[2, :] >= corner1[2]) & (coords[2, :] <= corner2[2]))
853
854        Xe_grid = Xe.ravel()[test]
855        Ye_grid = Ye.ravel()[test]
856        Ze_grid = Ze.ravel()[test]
857
858        X = np.array([Xe_grid, Ye_grid, Ze_grid]).T
859
860        tt_interp = tt_tmp_grid.interpolate(X, grid_space=False,
861                                            order=3)[0]
862
863        bias = np.max(tt_interp)
864
865        phi_out = np.ones_like(Xe).ravel()
866        phi_out[test] = tt_interp - bias
867
868        phi_out = phi_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
869
870        tt_out = skfmm.travel_time(phi_out, data, dx=spacing)
871
872        # tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
873        tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
874        tt_out[test] = tt_interp
875        tt_out = tt_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
876
877        tt_out_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_out, self.origin,
878                             self.spacing, seed, phase=self.phase,
879                             float_type=self.float_type,
880                             velocity_model_id=self.grid_id,
881                             label=self.label)
882
883        tt_out_grid.data -= tt_out_grid.interpolate(seed.T,
884                                                    grid_space=False,
885                                                    order=3)[0]
886
887        return tt_out_grid

889    def to_time_multi_threaded(self, seeds: SeedEnsemble, cpu_utilisation=0.9,
890                               *args, **kwargs):
891        """
892        Multithreaded version of the Eikonal solver
893        based on scikit fast marching solver
894        :param seeds: array of seed
895        :type seeds: np.ndarray
896        :param cpu_utilisation: fraction of the cpu core to be used for the
897        processing task (between 0 and 1)
898        :type cpu_utilisation: float between 0 and 1
899        :param args: arguments to be passed directly to skfmm.travel_time
900        function
901        :param kwargs: keyword arguments to be passed directly to
902        skfmm.travel_time function
903        :return: a travel time grid ensemble
904        :rtype: TravelTimeEnsemble
905        """
906
907        num_threads = int(np.ceil(cpu_utilisation * __cpu_count__))
908        # ensuring that the number of threads is comprised between 1 and
909        # __cpu_count__
910        num_threads = np.max([np.min([num_threads, __cpu_count__]), 1])
911
912        data = []
913        for seed in seeds:
914            if not self.in_grid(seed.loc):
915                logger.warning(f'{seed.label} is outside the grid. '
916                               f'The travel time grid will not be calculated')
917                continue
918
919        with Pool(num_threads) as pool:
920            results = pool.map(self.to_time, seeds)
921
922        tt_grid_ensemble = TravelTimeEnsemble(results)
923
924        return tt_grid_ensemble

def to_time( self, seed: Seed, sub_grid_resolution=0.1, *args, **kwargs): 
766    def to_time(self, seed: Seed, sub_grid_resolution=0.1,
767                *args, **kwargs):
768        """
769        Eikonal solver based on scikit fast marching solver
770        :param seed: numpy array location of the seed or origin of useis wave
771         in model coordinates
772        (usually location of a station or an event)
773        :type seed: numpy.ndarray or list
774        :param sub_grid_resolution: resolution of the grid around the seed.
775        Propagating the wavefront on a denser grid around the seed,
776        significantly improves the travel time accuracy. The value represents
777        a fraction of the grid resolution. For instance, assuming a grid with
778        spacing of 10m, if the sub_grid_resolution is set to 0.1, the
779        resolution around the grid will be 1m.
780
781        :rtype: TTGrid
782        """
783
784        if isinstance(seed, list):
785            seed = np.array(seed)
786
787        if not self.in_grid(seed.loc):
788            logger.warning(f'{seed.label} is outside the grid. '
789                           f'The travel time grid will not be calculated')
790            return
791
792        origin = self.origin
793        shape = self.shape
794        spacing = self.spacing
795
796        sub_grid_spacing = spacing * sub_grid_resolution
797
798        # extent = ((4 * sub_grid_spacing) * 1.2 + sub_grid_spacing)
799
800        n_pts_inner_grid = (4 * spacing / sub_grid_spacing * 1.2).astype(int)
801        for i in range(0, len(n_pts_inner_grid)):
802            if n_pts_inner_grid[i] % 2:
803                n_pts_inner_grid[i] += 1
804
805        x_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[0]) * sub_grid_spacing[0]
806        y_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[1]) * sub_grid_spacing[1]
807        z_i = np.arange(0, n_pts_inner_grid[2]) * sub_grid_spacing[2]
808
809        x_i = x_i - np.mean(x_i) + seed.x
810        y_i = y_i - np.mean(y_i) + seed.y
811        z_i = z_i - np.mean(z_i) + seed.z
812
813        X_i, Y_i, Z_i = np.meshgrid(x_i, y_i, z_i, indexing='ij')
814
815        coords = np.array([X_i.ravel(), Y_i.ravel(), Z_i.ravel()]).T
816
817        vel = self.interpolate(coords, grid_space=False).reshape(
818            X_i.shape)
819
820        phi = np.ones_like(X_i)
821        phi[int(np.floor(len(x_i) / 2)), int(np.floor(len(y_i) / 2)),
822            int(np.floor(len(z_i) / 2))] = 0
823
824        tt_tmp = skfmm.travel_time(phi, vel, dx=sub_grid_spacing)
825
826        tt_tmp_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_tmp, [x_i[0], y_i[0], z_i[0]],
827                             sub_grid_spacing, seed, self.grid_id,
828                             phase=self.phase,
829                             float_type=self.float_type, label=self.label)
830
831        # __init__(self, data_or_dims, origin, spacing, seed: Seed,
832        # phase: Phases = Phases.P, value: float = 0,
833        # float_type: FloatTypes = __default_float_type__,
834        # grid_id: ResourceIdentifier = ResourceIdentifier(),
835        # grid_units: GridUnits = __default_grid_units__):
836
837        data = self.data
838
839        xe = origin[0] + np.arange(0, shape[0], 1) * spacing[0]
840        ye = origin[1] + np.arange(0, shape[1], 1) * spacing[1]
841        ze = origin[2] + np.arange(0, shape[2], 1) * spacing[2]
842
843        Xe, Ye, Ze = np.meshgrid(xe, ye, ze, indexing='ij')
844
845        coords = np.array([Xe.ravel(), Ye.ravel(), Ze.ravel()])
846
847        corner1 = np.array([np.min(x_i), np.min(y_i), np.min(z_i)])
848        corner2 = np.array([np.max(x_i), np.max(y_i), np.max(z_i)])
849
850        test = ((coords[0, :] >= corner1[0]) & (coords[0, :] <= corner2[0]) &
851                (coords[1, :] >= corner1[1]) & (coords[1, :] <= corner2[1]) &
852                (coords[2, :] >= corner1[2]) & (coords[2, :] <= corner2[2]))
853
854        Xe_grid = Xe.ravel()[test]
855        Ye_grid = Ye.ravel()[test]
856        Ze_grid = Ze.ravel()[test]
857
858        X = np.array([Xe_grid, Ye_grid, Ze_grid]).T
859
860        tt_interp = tt_tmp_grid.interpolate(X, grid_space=False,
861                                            order=3)[0]
862
863        bias = np.max(tt_interp)
864
865        phi_out = np.ones_like(Xe).ravel()
866        phi_out[test] = tt_interp - bias
867
868        phi_out = phi_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
869
870        tt_out = skfmm.travel_time(phi_out, data, dx=spacing)
871
872        # tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
873        tt_out = tt_out.ravel() + bias
874        tt_out[test] = tt_interp
875        tt_out = tt_out.reshape(Xe.shape)
876
877        tt_out_grid = TTGrid(self.network_code, tt_out, self.origin,
878                             self.spacing, seed, phase=self.phase,
879                             float_type=self.float_type,
880                             velocity_model_id=self.grid_id,
881                             label=self.label)
882
883        tt_out_grid.data -= tt_out_grid.interpolate(seed.T,
884                                                    grid_space=False,
885                                                    order=3)[0]
886
887        return tt_out_grid

1291        """
1292        Combine a list of travel time grids together providing meta
1293        functionality (multithreaded ray tracing, sorting, travel-time
1294        calculation for a specific location etc.). It is assumed that
1295        all grids are compatible, i.e., that all the grids have the same
1296        origin, spacing and dimensions.
1297        :param travel_time_grids: a list of TTGrid objects
1298
1299        :NOTE: The travel time grids must all have the same grid labels if not,
1300        the object will not be created.
1301        """
1302
1303        self.travel_time_grids = []
1304        for travel_time_grid in travel_time_grids:
1305            if travel_time_grid.label != travel_time_grids[0].label:
1306                raise ValueError('all travel time grids must have the same '
1307                                 'label')

1309
1310        self.__i__ = 0
1311

1314                assert tt_grid.check_compatibility(travel_time_grids[0])
